The paper deals with logical relations, which are a fundamental tool in proving properties of lambda calculi. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with monadic types, which are a key feature of Moggi's computational lambda calculus. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also mentions non-determinism, dynamic name creation, and probabilistic systems, which suggests that it may belong to the Theory of Computation (cs.TL), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories, respectively.
